reviewText:
I normally wear a fanny pack. But my fanny pack is not as nice or as well made as this pack. I really like the light beige color and I can fit more than I thought in it (see photos). The belt is very very stretchy and can also be adjusted; at first I didn't think there was a buckle, but it's "hidden" inside a flap on the right side. The zippers are made so you really can't tell whether it's zipped or not until you put your finger on it. The back is a breathable and stretchy mesh. Inside the largest zipper enclosure is a couple different size pockets and a really nice carabiner to hold your keys.

The stitching is well done and it looks like it's made to last. It's also supposed to be water resistant but I haven't had the opportunity to test that. Add RFID blocking and you have a quality pack, waist wallet, money belt; whatever you want to call it.

{Product provided for my honest review. I only accept requests for products I can use}
